      "side": 1,
      "message": "Two phases:\n- if the user runs `cue` and there\u0027s no `cue.mod/plugin` directory but the code being evaluated uses `@extern(go)`, we\u0027ll get an error saying that Go plugins are used and we should invoke `cue plugin build`. (with the current PoC we get an error but not the suggestion to invoke `cue plugin build` - that will be fixed)\n- if the user runs `cue` and there\u0027s a `cue.mod/plugin` directory but no executable built, we get an `module uses plugins; build with \"cue plugin build\"` error\n\nI\u0027ve added a \"Bootstrapping\" section outlining the above.",
