      "lineNbr": 706,
      "author": {
        "id": 1017723
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-24T04:52:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Just to confirm my own understanding, the version of a Go function we resolve to (because of MVS there will only be one) is independent of the CUE instance and CUE module version, correct? i.e. all that ultimately matters is that some CUE code somewhere referenced that function (via its package).\n\nThe reason I ask is that it sounds like this map will have multiple entries for the same Go function, just with different keys.",
      "revId": "ce282b00d0f8779354a8e099c786d7ae80f9b149",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3cffa62f_12a8394a",
        "filename": "designs/XXXX-go-plugins.md",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 706,
      "author": {
        "id": 1007275
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-24T07:51:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes that\u0027s right. We can refer to a Go package both as `.` (the Go package in the current directory) or as a fully qualified import path. In the former case, the Go package we resolve to does depend on the CUE instance because that\u0027s the place where the import path of that directory is defined (via the `module` directive of the `go.mod` in some parent directory).\n\nDo you think this needs clarifying in the text?",
      "parentUuid": "fda2b718_dbb5bb99",
      "revId": "ce282b00d0f8779354a8e099c786d7ae80f9b149",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
